con:request.name: Create UpdateCF ScriptInstance
con:request.con:request:
<soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv="http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/" xmlns:ws="http://ws.api.meveo.org/">\r
   <soapenv:Header/>\r
   <soapenv:Body>\r
      <ws:create>\r
         <createScriptInstanceRequest code="org.meveo.service.script.The${#Project#entityPrefix}_${#TestSuite#index}_UpdateCF" description="Throw exception on customer update">\r
            <type>JAVA</type>\r
            <script>package org.meveo.service.script;

import java.util.Map;
import org.meveo.admin.exception.BusinessException;
import org.meveo.service.crm.impl.CustomFieldInstanceService;
import org.meveo.model.crm.Customer;
import org.meveo.service.script.Script;
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

public class The${#Project#entityPrefix}_${#TestSuite#index}_UpdateCF extends Script {
private static final Logger log = LoggerFactory.getLogger(The${#Project#entityPrefix}_${#TestSuite#index}_UpdateCF.class);
private CustomFieldInstanceService customFieldInstanceService = (CustomFieldInstanceService) getServiceInterface("CustomFieldInstanceService");

@Override
public void execute(Map<String, Object> methodContext) throws BusinessException {
	Customer customer = (Customer) methodContext.get("entity");
	log.debug("Customer {} : ", customer.getCode());
	customer.setDescription(customer.getDescription()+" from script");

	String cfValue = (String)customFieldInstanceService.getCFValue(customer, "${#Project#baseEntityPrefix}_CUST_STRING_SINGLE_NV");
	customFieldInstanceService.setCFValue(customer, "${#Project#baseEntityPrefix}_CUST_STRING_SINGLE_NV", cfValue+" from script");
	
}
}</script>\r
         </createScriptInstanceRequest>\r
      </ws:create>\r
   </soapenv:Body>\r
</soapenv:Envelope>
